1. *Olovka* je ostala na stolu. (The *pencil* remained on the table.)
2. Uzmi *olovku* i zapiši ovo. (Take the *pencil* and write this down.)
3. Proizvodim različite vrste *olovaka*. (I manufacture different types of *pencils*.)
4. Da li imaš oštru *olovku*? (Do you have a sharp *pencil*?)
5. Vidim da ti je *olovka* pala na pod. (I see that your *pencil* fell on the floor.)
6. Nisam siguran gde sam ostavio svoju *olovku*. (I'm not sure where I left my *pencil*.)
7. Želela bih da kupim novu *olovku* za pisanje. (I would like to buy a new *pencil* for writing.)
8. *Olovkom* sam napisao pismo. (I wrote the letter with a *pencil*.)
9. Molim te, pozajmi mi tvoju *olovku*. (Please lend me your *pencil*.)
10. Kada učim, uvek držim *olovku* u ruci. (When I study, I always hold a *pencil* in my hand.)

Note: The word "olovka" in Serbian refers to a pencil, which is a writing instrument typically made of graphite and wood. The word can also be used in its instrumental form "olovkom", which means "with a pencil".